We are there with you every step of the way on your journey to emotional health. To ensure a seamless experience we have resolved some bugs and introduced enhancements to improve the speed performance and reliability of the app with this update.

Hey there! We ve updated the MindDoc app with bug fixes and small improvements to make your experience even smoother. Plus we ve added a new feature that allows you to share feedback on the app right from the profile tab. Enjoy using the app and take care!

Thank you very much how wonderful that you re using MindDoc! With this update completing course chapters and exercises will become easier. We have also fixed some minor bugs and improved the performance and reliability of the app.

As your companion we strive to provide you with fresh inspiration along the way. With this update you will find course recommendations on the Home tab that match your interests. When you start a new course you will also find the next chapters on the Home tab under From Active Courses . Need a break or some variety You can simply pause active courses and resume them later by opening the course in the Discover section and completing a chapter. Your progress will always be saved.

We ve completely redesigned the Home to allow you to focus more easily on what s important. You now get an overview of what s planned for the day and can see what you ve completed. All Insights are here for greater convenience. The calendar icon at top left is where you can find all previous entries. Feel free to contact us with any questions or suggestions!

Better overview on insights and courses. With this update you ll see your daily insights grouped together and within our courses it will be easier to navigate thanks to new sections we will introduce step by step. We have also worked on the stability of the app and from now on inform more clearly when redirecting you to external offers within the app.
This update fixes a bug for iOS 13 when launching the app.

This update includes a fresh and modern version of our initial launch process when you are new to MindDoc. It s now also clearer for MindDoc account users to see why they were logged out. In addition we ve simplified the way we configure push notifications so you get them more reliably.
This update includes some invisible but important stability improvements and fixes some minor bugs.
This update contains improvements and bug fixes. Also you can withdraw your consent to crash analytics in the settings view with this version.

This update contains improvements and bug fixes. The result countdown is now loaded instantly again. Also you now can navigate within the free text field in the journal entry without problems again and all email addresses are accepted during registration.
This update contains improvements and bug fixes that solve some problems that sometimes have set back the data when users updated the app.
With this version we have improved the stability of the app fixed a few small bugs and improved the way you can edit previous entries in the Journal so that MindDoc remains your reliable companion.

Happy and healthy New Year!. The app navigation now shows separate areas for your results and treatment options that go beyond the MindDoc app. We ve also made technical and visual improvements and fixed some bugs to make things like Push Notifications work more reliably.
We implemented a minor stability improvement when opening the app from the background and changed some text to make to ensure MindDoc can reliably accompany you into 2021.
This update fixes some minor bugs.

To make MindDoc a more reliable companion for your emotional wellbeing we fixed a bug where Push Notifications and wake up time have been deactivated or set back when users logged in from the onboarding view. We also removed some deprecated features.
We fixed a bug that caused Push Notifications to be deactivated for users updating from version 4.0.0
This update contains improvements and bug fixes that solve some problems that occurred during the registration process.

Moodpath turns into MindDoc. It remains your companion for your emotional health. With this update and the re branding the app gains the following new features and improvements: Your personal MindDoc account is here! From now on you can register in the app with your email address and a password and use it to protect your data even if you change your device From now on your 14 day evaluations will be general reports on your emotional health as a whole and will no longer focus on depression. You will continue to see all the details of your responses and recommendations for further steps Besides that we have implemented some improvements and updates to make the app even more stable and secure. If you have any questions or requests please feel free to contact us at feedback minddoc.de.

From now on you can add entries retroactively and also edit previous entries. This enables you to record important events or changes in your mood in retrospect and to correct inaccurate entries.

This update brings a fix to the push notification settings and an explanation for when to expect to receive new questions by tapping on the timer on your day view. We hope Moodpath is helping a bit in coping with these extraordinary times. Stay safe!

This release introduces a short explanation text for each question we ask. We re aware how personal our questions can be and want to give you some context of why each question is relevant for us to ask. Let us know if you find them helpful or not!

Don t have more than a few bug fixes and impovements for you. Stay tuned for more...
This update will bring some small fixes to the tags and lots of technical fixes to make the app run smoother

We received lots of feedback on the tags feature and have made some changes! We brought back the pre selection to let you scan through them and reflect about the good and the bad for each entry. You can still add your own custom tags of course. We also fixed a few issues in the Discover area for you!

You asked we listened: Custom reminder notification settings are finally here. You can now decide when you want to be reminded about new questions. We also made it easier to start a online therapy with MindDoc only in Germany and added a couple of other small improvements and bug fixes.
Sure we fixed several bugs and polished a few things but that s not all! This update brings a whole new mood tracking experience and the ability to export your Doctor Letter in different languages.

Many of you let us know that push notifications weren t as reliable as they should have been. That changes with this update and you should receive them without any issues now. We also fixed a couple of things under the hood. We re very thankful for your input. Please keep letting us know about your feedback and ideas!

Friends it s time for an update: New stats! You were asking for better statistics and they re finally here. Tap Statistics on each month to see your mood graph your top moods and much more. Result generation got a facelift. Next time Moodpath generates a new result for you you ll see a nice little animation and a quick way to open it directly after answering questions. Thoughts ideas or just a fun story you want to share Let us know: feedback moodpath.de

With this update we re introducing two new features for you Courses and Insights . COURSES give you access to our library of interactive psychological exercises around the topics of rumination self worth and mindfulness. Month by month we ll be adding new exercises and courses to the library so that you will have a lot to explore. INSIGHTS will replace the statistics tab in the main navigation and provide interesting and helpful information into your moods thoughts feelings and experiences. They should help you to better understand your thought patterns and triggers of depressive symptoms. Every Monday there will be a weekly stats insight summarizing your last week with all your entries in a nice overview. We hope you ll enjoy the update! Your Moodpath team.
